<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Home Page</title>
    <style>
        body {
            height: 100%; /* Set body height to fill the viewport */
            margin: 0; /* Remove default margin */
            background: linear-gradient(87.4deg, rgb(190, 227, 246) 1.9%, rgb(135, 225, 243) 49.7%, rgb(2, 230, 255) 100.5%);
            position: relative; /* Position relative to allow absolute positioning of hearts */
        }

        main {
            text-align: center;
            padding-top: 5%;
            font-size: larger;
        }

        /* Style for heart images */
        .heart {
            position: absolute;
            width: 20px; /* Adjust size as needed */
            height: auto; /* Maintain aspect ratio */
            z-index: -1; /* Ensure hearts are behind content */
        }

        /* Position heart images around the background */
        .heart:nth-child(1) {
            top: 20%;
            left: 10%;
        }

        .heart:nth-child(2) {
            top: 60%;
            left: 30%;
        }

        .heart:nth-child(3) {
            top: 80%;
            left: 70%;
        }

        /* Add more .heart:nth-child() rules as needed */
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <main>
        <div class="jumbotron jumbotron-fluid">
            <div class="container">
                <h1 class="display-4"><b>Home Page</b></h1>
                <p>Welcome, this is the home page. My name is Anees and I'm happy to show you my first HTML website with Node.js and Express.js. <br> This website entails some of the work I've done, a brief introduction, and a way to contact me. Enjoy. <br> Sincerely, Anees</p>
                <p> <br>  <b>Above you have three different sections:</b> <br> <b>Projects: Which are some projects I have previously worked on <br> <b>About me: A small introduction video <br> <b> Contact: Information on how to contact me </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </main>

    <!-- Heart images -->
    <img src="/assets/images/heart.png" class="heart" alt="Heart image">
    <!-- Add more heart images as needed -->

</body>
</html>
